data.description: This 2 Bedroom Cottage is absolutely Beautiful but it needs approximately $290k worth of work to make it livable according to estimates given by contractors. It's location is perfect looking down on the most calming stream that runs along Lompico Road. Although home has been damaged by the most recent winter storms that hit Santa Cruz Mountains, it truly has amazing potential for a contractor, investor or a buyer that may qualify for a Rehab Loan. This home has been Red Tagged by the County due to Backside retaining wall giving way to a mudslide damaging the back wall of the home. The damage includes one of the bedrooms and a linen/coat closet in the living space. There is also water damage to the floors throughout the living space and the finished basement  caused by the Skylights being damaged and leaking throughout the storm.
